				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathcal {D} = \{\mathcal {D}_L \cup \mathcal {D}_U\}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M58"><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="script">D</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mo stretchy="false">{</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">D</mml:mi><mml:mi>L</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x0222a;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">D</mml:mi><mml:mi>U</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">}</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq48.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> can be seen as a combination of two samples: the labelled <inline-formula id="IEq49"><alternatives><tex-math id="M59">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
