				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$s=1$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M90"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>s</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq64.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, otherwise it is labelled as &#x0201c;missing&#x0201d;. So what we actually can observe is not <italic>Y</italic>, but a &#x0201c;surrogate&#x0201d; variable <inline-formula id="IEq65"><alternatives><tex-math id="M91">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
