				\begin{document}$$1-\alpha $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M202"><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">&#x003b1;</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq122.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> in order for the tests to be valid, while elsewhere the plots indicate the <italic>False&#x000a0;Negative&#x000a0;Rate</italic>. Figure&#x000a0;<xref rid="Fig3" ref-type="fig">3</xref> verifies Theorem <xref ref-type="sec" rid="FPar3">1</xref>, by showing that the surrogate tests are valid, since all lines have the same intercept at <inline-formula id="IEq123"><alternatives><tex-math id="M203">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
