				\begin{document}$$p(y=1)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M220"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>p</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>y</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq131.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. From the above theorem, we observe that by using <italic>&#x0201c;exact&#x0201d; prior knowledge</italic> over <inline-formula id="IEq132"><alternatives><tex-math id="M221">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
