				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\widetilde{Y}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M384"><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>Y</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="true">~</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq231.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. We say that the two approaches <inline-formula id="IEq232"><alternatives><tex-math id="M385">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
