				\begin{document}$$I(X_k;Y).$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M474"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>I</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mi>k</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x0037e;</mml:mo><mml:mi>Y</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo><mml:mo>.</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq273.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> More advanced criteria rank the features using higher-order conditional mutual information terms, i.e. JMI ranks the features by estimating <inline-formula id="IEq274"><alternatives><tex-math id="M475">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
