				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\widetilde{Y}_0}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M510"><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>Y</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="true">~</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq310.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. This figure also verifies Theorem <xref ref-type="sec" rid="FPar17">7</xref>, where we see that the number of variables falsely removed when using the surrogate test <inline-formula id="IEq311"><alternatives><tex-math id="M511">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
