</p><p id="Par121">Now, let us assume we have semi-supervised data under the class-prior-change scenario (for more details see Sect.&#x000a0;<xref rid="Sec8" ref-type="sec">2.3</xref>), or in other words the labels are MAR-C. In our simulation we sample the labelled data in order to have a class ratio in the labelled set inverse than the population ratio: <inline-formula id="IEq331"><alternatives><tex-math id="M551">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
