				\begin{document}$$\hat{p}(x,y)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M646"><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>p</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>x</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>y</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq378.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the maximum-likelihood estimate of the probability that the random variable <italic>X</italic> takes on the value <italic>x</italic> from its alphabet <inline-formula id="IEq379"><alternatives><tex-math id="M647">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
