"/></disp-formula>From this expression we see the relationship between the <italic>G</italic>-statistic and MI, and the latter can be seen as the natural unit of <italic>effect size</italic> for the <italic>G</italic>-test (Rosenthal et&#x000a0;al. <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR38">2000</xref>). Under the null hypothesis (<inline-formula id="IEq398"><alternatives><tex-math id="M681">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
