				\begin{document}$$\chi ^2$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M690"><mml:msup><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">&#x003c7;</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq403.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>-distribution. The <italic>p</italic>-value represents the probability of obtaining a test statistic equal or more extreme than the observed one, given that the null hypothesis holds. After calculating this value, we check to see whether it exceeds a user specified significance level <inline-formula id="IEq404"><alternatives><tex-math id="M691">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\alpha $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M692"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">&#x003b1;</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq404.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. If <inline-formula id="IEq405"><alternatives><tex-math id="M693">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
