				\begin{document}$$\chi ^2$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M706"><mml:msup><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">&#x003c7;</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq411.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> distribution under the alternative hypothesis (Agresti <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR1">2013</xref>,&#x000a0;Section 6.6.4), with the same degrees of freedom as in the null distribution. The non-centrality parameter &#x02013;<inline-formula id="IEq412"><alternatives><tex-math id="M707">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
