				\begin{document}$$\mathbf{Surrogate~1}~(\mathcal {D}_L)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M718"><mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="bold">Surrogate</mml:mi><mml:mspace width="3.33333pt"/><mml:mn mathvariant="bold">1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mspace width="3.33333pt"/><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">D</mml:mi><mml:mi>L</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq419.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>: To prove <inline-formula id="IEq420"><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_IEq420_HTML.gif"/></inline-formula>, we need to prove:<disp-formula id="Equ24"><alternatives><tex-math id="M719">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
