				\begin{document}$$p(s=1)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M742"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>p</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>s</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq429.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, while 2<italic>NI</italic>(<italic>X</italic>;&#x000a0;<italic>Y</italic>) is the non-centrality parameter of the unobservable test. Thus <inline-formula id="IEq430"><alternatives><tex-math id="M743">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
