				\begin{document}$$X,{\widetilde{Y}_0}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M754"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>Y</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="true">~</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Article_IEq435.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and <italic>X</italic>,&#x000a0;<italic>Y</italic>, we can explore the relationship between the non-centrality parameters of the <inline-formula id="IEq436"><alternatives><tex-math id="M755">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
