<disp-formula id="Equ46"><graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Equ46_HTML.gif" position="anchor"/></disp-formula>
</p></sec><sec id="FPar23"><title>Proof</title><p id="Par179">To prove this Lemma we will start from the <italic>RHS</italic> of the desired equation:<disp-formula id="Equ47"><graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Equ47_HTML.gif" position="anchor"/></disp-formula>Then by using the Bayes theorem and the chain rule we get:<disp-formula id="Equ48"><graphic xlink:href="10994_2017_5648_Equ48_HTML.gif" position="anchor"/></disp-formula>Because of MAR-C assumption:<disp-formula id="Equ14"><label>14</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M853">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
